  note = {Hypothesis paper proposing that beta2-adrenergic receptor dysfunction leads to insufficient Na+/K+-ATPase stimulation, causing intracellular sodium overload. At elevated sodium concentrations, the sodium-calcium exchanger (NCX) reverses to import calcium rather than export it, causing calcium overload and mitochondrial dysfunction. This creates a vicious cycle explaining PEM and exercise intolerance}
