  note    = {CSF proteomics (890 proteins, LC-MS) in 48 HSE patients at 3 time points. T1 (0--9 days): strong acute phase, antimicrobial, glycolysis pathway activation. Six proteins significantly reduced in anti-NMDAR seropositive patients: procathepsin H, heparin cofactor 2, complement factor I, protein AMBP, apolipoprotein A1, and polymeric immunoglobulin receptor. ApoA1 previously linked to NMDAR encephalitis. ME/CFS CRC at Harvard co-authored; OMF-funded.}
