  pmid    = {39596903},
  note    = {Long COVID patients showed 20.8 ± 10.7\% morphologically abnormal RBCs vs 2.9 ± 1.5\% in controls; echinocytes/acanthocytes 16.0 ± 9.9\% vs 2.3 ± 1.4\%. Aggregation index substantially elevated. Samples taken at average 42 weeks post-infection — beyond the 120-day RBC lifespan — indicating ongoing generation of abnormal RBCs, not survival of initially damaged cells. Moderate negative correlation between RBC morphological abnormalities and fatigue severity (r = −0.5131, p = 0.0061).},
