  pmcid    = {PMC7136523},
  keywords = {ME/CFS, anti-mitochondrial antibody, AMA, anti-PDC, anti-cardiolipin, metabolic dysfunction, null finding, primary biliary cholangitis, PBC},
  note     = {Cross-sectional study; 161 ME/CFS patients across 3 cohorts + controls (44 healthy donors, 15 PBC, 14 fibromyalgia, 29 MS). Antibodies tested: anti-PDC (pyruvate dehydrogenase complex), general AMA (inner/outer mitochondrial membrane by IIF), anti-cardiolipin (IgG/IgM/IgA). Results: only 1/161 ME/CFS patients positive for anti-PDC (vs.\ 15/15 PBC patients). General AMA negative in ME/CFS cohort. Anti-cardiolipin not significantly different from healthy donors. CRITICAL CAVEAT: anti-ANT was NOT specifically tested in this study. The study tests general inner mitochondrial membrane AMA by IIF, which may not detect ANT-specific antibodies with sufficient sensitivity. Conclusion: metabolic dysfunction in ME/CFS is not explained by the anti-mitochondrial autoantibodies tested. G28 gap remains open because this paper did not use ANT-specific ELISA. Limitations: anti-ANT not tested with isoform-specific assay; IIF may miss low-titre ANT-specific antibodies.},
  certainty = {0.70},
