  pmid     = {32327453},
  keywords = {ME/CFS, HHV-6, mitochondrial fragmentation, DRP1, energy metabolism, cell danger response, Prusty, Naviaux},
  note     = {Mechanistic study; n=10 ME/CFS patient serum samples tested in cell culture assays. HHV-6 reactivation associated with mitochondrial fragmentation via miR-aU14/miR-30/p53/DRP1 axis. Adoptive transfer of ME/CFS patient serum reproduced mitochondrial fragmentation and antiviral state in recipient cells. Mitochondrial fragmentation causes severe metabolic dysfunction: pyruvate dehydrogenase and fatty acid oxidation enzymes strongly inhibited; 1-carbon metabolism and thymidylate synthase induced. Does not directly measure ANT or ATP export. However, mitochondrial fragmentation disrupts cristae organisation and may impair ANT function indirectly by destabilising the ATP synthasome. Limitations: n=10; in vitro serum transfer model; HHV-6 mechanism not confirmed in all ME/CFS patients; ANT not directly assessed.},
